		<title>06EMPLOYMENT</title>
		<content>      The main work provided by the    
 area is hill sheep-farming, with some 
 dairy and beef-cattle raising, but    
 farming is not the mainstay. Murton   
 has an agricultural engineer, Hilton a
 haulage contracting business. One     
 farmer runs a pony-trekking centre and
 also breeds horses for harness-racing.
 Many people travel to work to nearby  
 Appleby, five miles distant, or drive 
 the l8 miles to Penrith, or even some 
 30 miles to Carlisle or Kendal.       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
